            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d43e181" publication-type="other">
This is also the weakness of the more sophisticated variant of this argument — the Ramsey rules. Life is
the most inelastically demanded commodity of all, and if a uniform lump sum tax is possible, as it
certainly is, then there is no role for Ramsey taxes.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
